$ SQL Server - sys.columns
@ sys.columns

Joining → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/tables[`sys.tables`] with `sys.columns` allows to query table and column names.

{ Showing columns of a table

   The following query displays the → development/databases/SQL-Server/objects/table/column[columns] and → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types[datatypes] of a given → development/databases/SQL-Server/objects/table:
   gh|about-MSSQL|/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/columns/table-columns.sql||

   Compare with → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/INFORMATION_SCHEMA/columns[INFORMATION_SCHEMA.columns] and
   → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/stored-procedures/sp_columns[`sp_columns`].

}
{ Find tables by column name #find-tables-by-column-name

  A similar query finds all tables that have a column whose name matches a given pattern:
  gh|about-MSSQL|/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/columns/find-tables-by-column-name.sql||


}

sa:

  See also → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas#mssql-search-object[query objects in a schema] to find any object by its name.

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/syscolumns[`sys.syscolumns`] and
  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/all_columns[`sys.all_columns`].

  The → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys[sys schema].
